{
  "answer": "**Chapter 6 of *Traité de Législation: VOL IV* by Charles Comte is titled \"De l’influence de l’esclavage sur les mœurs des Romains.\"** (English translation: \"On the influence of slavery on the morals of the Romans,\" where *moeurs* refers to manners, customs, or morals.)[^1]\n\nThis chapter examines how domestic slavery corrupted Roman society across classes, from patricians to slaves. Key effects include intellectual stagnation, love of idleness and luxury, sexual licentiousness, passion for violent spectacles like gladiatorial combats, cruelty in punishments, aristocratic pride, and perfidy in politics.[^1]\n\nThe full English translation is available in the corpus.[^1]\n\n[^1]: Charles Comte, *Traité de Législation: VOL IV*, [Chapter 6](/works/charles-comte-traite-de-legislation-vol-iv-bca040/06-de-l-influence-de-l-esclavage-sur-les-moeurs-des-r/translation/).",
